  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Solution Description&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Application Transformation extends the life and value of a business solution by:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Helping teams to discover and unlock the business value in their legacy applications.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Preserving the existing business logic, while re-implementing it to make key functions more easily accessible.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Improving maintainability by re-implementing the application with modern languages and tools such as Java and EGL,&#xD;
        while preserving the integrity and quality of service the business requires.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Symptoms&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Fragile or brittle application architecture.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Concerns about the&amp;nbsp;team's ability to deliver value to the business with&amp;nbsp;existing architecture.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Evolving business models causing requirements for new portals.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Increasing difficulty&amp;nbsp;in meeting schedule and budget commitments.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Issues with turnover and deployment.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
